# Auto commit & deploy — Delphi (Cosmos Prowler)

After completing substantive work in this repo, **commit and push without asking**.

## When to commit

- Bug fixes, features, refactors, or config changes under `agent/web/`, root scripts, or deploy files
- Do **not** commit secrets (`.env.local`, API keys, Netlify tokens)
- Do **not** commit unless there are real changes (no empty commits)

## Workflow

1. `git status` and `git diff` — stage only files related to the task
2. Write a concise commit message (1–2 sentences, focus on why)
3. `git add` → `git commit` → `git push origin main`
4. Briefly tell the user: commit hash, that push succeeded, and which deploy target updated — **Vercel** (`https://delphi-wine.vercel.app`) via `.github/workflows/vercel-deploy.yml`, or Netlify if secrets are configured.

## Remote

- Repo: `https://github.com/paulooventura/DELPHI.git`
- Branch: `main`

## Do not

- Force-push, amend pushed commits, or skip hooks unless the user explicitly asks
- Push `.env*` or credential files
